<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-019-048  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 019 048.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer Systems News  Jan 8 1990 n449 p1(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Bells hear new ring: integration! (part 1) (includes relatedarticle on businesses the Bells are barred from) (Bell regionalholding companies)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Race, Tim.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The Bell regional holding companies, notably Nynex Corp, PacificBell and Ameritech, are making systems integration applications amajor part of their strategic planning.andP;  Gad Selig, vice presidentof Nynex's systems integration group, says that networking andcommunications will dominate the systems integration of thefuture.andP;  Nynex recently headed a $33.5 million project to installcredit-card payment systems in the parking facilities of NewYork's three airports.andP;  Pacific Bell intends to market a varietyof data communications equipment, networking and consultingservices.andP;  Ameritech is bidding to build a $20 million OnlineComputer Library Center that will link 17 Ohio Universities.andP;  Thevalue of the systems integration market is currently $10 billion,and it is expected to grow to $28.8 billion by 1994.andP;  The RBOCsface competition from established systems integrators such as IBM.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Bell Regional Holding CompaniesStrategic PlanningComputer Systems IntegratorsIntegrated Voice-DataTelecommunicationsCompetition.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>